ZH: 我们要去戏台看戏。
EN: We are going to the theater to watch a play.

ZH: 在戏台上演出的是一出悲剧。
EN: The play being performed on the theater stage is a tragedy.

ZH: 他正在戏台上扮演一个勇敢的英雄角色。
EN: He is playing the role of a brave hero on the theater stage.

ZH: 我们坐在戏台前排的位置上。
EN: We are sitting in the front row of the theater stage.

ZH: 戏台上的灯光闪耀着奇异的色彩。
EN: The lights on the theater stage are shining with strange colors.

ZH: 音乐响起，演员们走上了戏台。
EN: The music starts playing, and the actors walk onto the theater stage.

ZH: 演员们在戏台上跳起了舞蹈。
EN: The actors are dancing on the theater stage.

ZH: 我喜欢在戏台上表演我的才艺。
EN: I enjoy showcasing my talents on the theater stage.

ZH: 每个星期五晚上在戏台举行一场音乐会。
EN: There is a concert held on the theater stage every Friday night.

ZH: 戏台上的装饰物让整个场景更加华丽。
EN: The decorations on the theater stage make the whole scene more magnificent.

ZH: 他花了整个暑假在戏台上排练。
EN: He spent the entire summer rehearsing on the theater stage.

ZH: 我梦想着有一天能站在戏台上。
EN: I dream of standing on the theater stage one day.

ZH: 她的演出在戏台上赢得了观众们的热烈掌声。
EN: Her performance on the theater stage received enthusiastic applause from the audience.

ZH: 我们在戏台后面搭建了一个幕布。
EN: We set up a curtain behind the theater stage.

ZH: 演员们在戏台上旋转和跳跃。
EN: The actors are spinning and jumping on the theater stage.

ZH: 每年都会在这个戏台上举行一个文化节。
EN: A cultural festival is held on this theater stage every year.

ZH: 我们在戏台周围摆放了屏风和鲜花。
EN: Screens and flowers were placed around the theater stage.

ZH: 他在戏台上演出时失去了台词。
EN: He forgot his lines while performing on the theater stage.

ZH: 我们在戏台上看了一部引人入胜的戏剧。
EN: We watched a gripping drama on the theater stage.

ZH: 每个演员都渴望在戏台上亮相。
EN: Every actor aspires to perform on the theater stage.
